# Auto Pipeline — Implementation Plan

## Goal
Build [auto_pipeline.py](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/auto_pipeline.py): a single Python script that replaces the manual Jupyter
workflow. It fetches fresh data from the two ArcGIS REST APIs, then runs every step
of [development.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/development.ipynb) in order, producing the same output files the dashboard expects.

---

## What I Observed in [development.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/development.ipynb)

The notebook has **4 code cells**, in this exact order:

| Cell | What it does | Reads | Writes |
|------|-------------|-------|--------|
| **Cell 1** | Clean 311 requests | [311_requests_full.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/311_requests_full.csv) | [311_requests_cleaned.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/311_requests_cleaned.csv) |
| **Cell 2** | Clean code violations | [montgomery_code_violations_full.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/montgomery_code_violations_full.csv) | [violations_cleaned.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/violations_cleaned.csv) |
| **Cell 3** | Clean weather sirens | [Weather_Sirens.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/Weather_Sirens.csv) | [sirens_cleaned.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/sirens_cleaned.csv) |
| **Cell 4** | Feature engineering → feature matrix | `*_cleaned.csv` files | [feature_matrix.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/feature_matrix.csv) |
| **Cell 5** | Train RF model + score + save | [feature_matrix.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/feature_matrix.csv) | [nuisance_predictor.pkl](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/nuisance_predictor.pkl), [risk_scores.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/risk_scores.csv), [feature_importance.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/feature_importance.csv), [model_evaluation.png](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/model_evaluation.png) |

The auto pipeline will:
1. **Prepend**: fetch fresh 311 + violations data from APIs → save as `*_full.csv`
2. **Then run** each of the 5 notebook cells' logic verbatim as Python functions

