## Proposed Changes

### [DELETE] [auto_pipeline.py](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/auto_pipeline.py)
Delete the version I already wrote (it diverges from the notebook).

---

### [NEW] [auto_pipeline.py](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/auto_pipeline.py)

The new script will contain 7 sequential functions that mirror the notebook exactly:

```
step0_fetch_api()          ← NEW: paginate ArcGIS REST APIs, save *_full.csv
step1_clean_311()          ← Exact copy of Cell 1 logic
step2_clean_violations()   ← Exact copy of Cell 2 logic
step3_clean_sirens()       ← Exact copy of Cell 3 logic
step4_feature_matrix()     ← Exact copy of Cell 4 logic
step5_train_and_score()    ← Exact copy of Cell 5 logic
main()                     ← Calls all steps in order, logs timing
```

**Key design decisions:**
- Every function is a verbatim port of the corresponding notebook cell  
  (same variable names, same column names, same thresholds, same file paths)
- API fetch uses `resultOffset` pagination (ArcGIS standard), max 2000 rows/page
- If the API is unreachable, it falls back to the existing `*_full.csv` on disk so the rest of the pipeline still runs
- Siren data is static (no API) — just re-runs Cell 3 cleaning from [Weather_Sirens.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/Weather_Sirens.csv)
- All output paths are identical to the notebook ([Dataset/risk_scores.csv](file:///c:/Users/Acer/Desktop/Project/Hackathon/Dataset/risk_scores.csv), etc.)
- Script can be run at any time to refresh data + retrain

